==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rosefish
<hw>Rose"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large marine scorpaenoid food fish (<spn>Sebastes marinus</spn>)
found on the northern coasts of Europe and America. called also
<altname>red perch</altname>, <altname>hemdurgan</altname>,
<altname>Norway haddok</altname>, and also, erroneously,
<altname>snapper</altname>, <altname>bream</altname>, and
<altname>bergylt</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ When full grown it is usually bright rose-red or
orange-red; the young are usually mottled with red and ducky
brown.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rosehead</ent>⟦br⟧
